Package: Heartbeat
Title: Run Heartbeat Analysis on numerical Likert Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Patrick", "Green", , "patrickagreen93@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Christopher", "Patton", role = "aut"),
    person("Justin", "Purl", role = "aut")
  )
Description: A simple package to conduct Heartbeat Analysis on Likert data
    and produce a data.frame ready to be presented as a table or developed
    further in a graphic. Heartbeat Analysis is a method of reporting
    sentiment developed by Christopher Patton and Justin Purl, presented
    at SIOP 2021.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    tidyr
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    ggplot2
VignetteBuilder: 
    knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.0.9000
URL: https://github.com/PatrickGreen93/Heartbeat
BugReports: https://github.com/PatrickGreen93/Heartbeat/issues
